After three years search for justice, reprieve finally came the way of veteran image-maker, Ernest Omo-Ojo following the successful mediation by the Minister of State Petroleum Resources Chief Timipre Sylva leading to the withdrawal of the sack letter issued to him in June 2019 by Mobil Producing Nigeria Unlimited, a subsidiary of ExxonMobil.   And God decided to show up, by Femi Adesina     Sen. Uba Sani wins Kaduna APC Gov ticket     Yilwada clinches Plateau APC Gov ticket   Acting swiftly on a petition dispatched to his office by Omo-Ojo to protest the seeming arbitrary termination of his appointment by the multinational oil corporation, the Minister in July last year, inaugurated a three-man committee, all directors, from the Ministry to investigate the matter and make recommendations to his office. His Special Adviser on Media, Mr. Horatious Egua confirmed that his principal had in 2022 intervened in between the firm and Omo-Ojo.